CRITICAL CLARIFICATIONS & FOLLOW-UPS On Melody Parameters (Your opening question) You asked: "I want to be able to choose if I want melodies more plucky, gliding, etc. Are you sure all these things will be possible to create?"

Short answer: YES, but with caveats.

Melody characteristics like "plucky" (short, percussive attack) vs. "gliding" (smooth portamento) are absolutely controllable through:

MIDI note velocity (plucky = sharp, gliding = smooth) Pitch bend data (gliding uses pitch bend curves) Duration/envelope (plucky = short decay, gliding = longer sustain) Articulation data (separate note events vs. legato) BUT — these require specific rendering engines. A piano roll alone can't express these. You need:

A voice synth/sampler (if generating vocal toplines) Instrument-specific rendering (Serum behaves differently than a sampler) Real-time synthesis or sample-based playback QUESTION: Melody Rendering

